However, the vast majority, even those who are educated understand the right of men in El Salvador to be aggressive they are unaware and embarrassed that it is an abusive behaviour. In regards to the question of “why,” there are most certainly factors contributing to the inclination of Salvadoran women to be subservient. Part of it stems from the cultural dynamic of de facto (and de jure during the civil war) machismo, however; another if not greater driving force is simply that women don’t have many options open to them. To improve the rate of marriage equality, El Salvador needs to encourage education amongst its youth, most especially women.
